NAME
  clm

SYNOPSIS
  clm column [options]+

DESCRIPTION
  get only a particular column from STDIN

PARAMETERS
  column (1 -> int(column)) 
      column number 
  --compressed, -c 
      compress all into one line 
  --help, -h 

AUTHOR
  jorrel ang

EXAMPLES
  $ ps aux | clm 11
  - fetch only the 11th column from the output of ps aux
  
  $ gem list | clm 1 --compressed
  - get all installed gems separated by spaces

